  "text": "Recognising the needs of the growing population of older people, various initiatives have been taken at national as well as EU level to improve accessibility and affordability as reported in the earlier sections. However, these measures often attempt to address the requirements considering older people as a homogeneous cohort. In fact, there are differences among older people themselves in terms of their physical abilities or living situations who hence have different requirements of public transport. To analyse these issues in more depth, the cohort of older people was divided into five different profiles in the GOAL project on the basis of different levels of health and mobility. These profiles, are more fully described in [CITATION_1] ). These five profiles are used as the basis for analysing the requirements in more detail.",
